@NODE "KeyStrokes" "Keyboard shortcuts"

   The @{B}AmigaTalk@{UB} Programming window (the top one), @{I}when active@{UI}, will 
   recognize the following keystrokes:
    
      '?', Help key, 'h' or 'H' -- Same as the @{" Help menu item " LINK "HelpMI"}

      'q', 'Q', 'x' or 'X' -- Same as the @{" Quit menu item " LINK "QuitMI"}

      'i' or 'I' -- Same as the @{" About menu item " LINK "AboutMI"}

      'l' or 'L' -- Same as the @{" Load menu item " LINK "LoadMI"}

      's' or 'S' -- Same as the @{" Save menu item " LINK "SaveMI"}

      'a' or 'A' -- Same as the @{" Save As menu item " LINK "SaveAsMI"}

      'u' or 'U' -- Same as the @{" Add User Script...    " LINK "AddUserScript"}

      'r' or 'R' -- Same as the @{" Remove User Script... " LINK "RemoveUserScript"}

      'b' or 'B' -- Same as the @{" Open Browser menu item " LINK "OpenBrowserMI"}

      'e' or 'E' -- Same as the @{" Edit a File  menu item " LINK "EditaFileMI"}

      't' or 'T' -- See the @{" Trace menu item " LINK "TraceMI"}

      'f1'       -- Display a summary of the System Directives.
@ENDNODE

