@NODE requirement "AmigaTalk requirements:"
@NEXT distribution
@PREV main

   @{B}REQUIREMENTS
   ~~~~~~~~~~~~@{UB}
   
   68040 or better microprocessor.
   (68000 or 68020 versions available upon request) 

   20+ MB of Memory (or you can edit the InitializeCommands script file &
                     delete the instantiation of Intuition, DataTypeSystem 
                     & DosSystem classes, if present)

   Memory usage has become an issue for the Program.  I had to
   re-write the original memory management functions so that they
   actually free memory when the Program exits.  You now have to
   set 5 ToolTypes in the Icon in order to create enough space for the
   various Objects that the Program will create.  If your PC has
   less than 20 Mb of RAM available, you might not be able to use
   this Program for complex operations anymore. 

   The following @{" ToolTypes " LINK "ToolTypes"} determine how much Memory AmigaTalk will
   look for @{FG SHINE}(These are the minimums that are hard-coded in AmigaTalk): @{FG TEXT}
   
   ToolType:             Default: Object Size:
   ~~~~~~~~~             ~~~~~~~~ ~~~~~~~~~~~~
   ObjectTableSize      =2000000  Varies   (I recommend at least 10,000,000!)
   ByteArrayTableSize   =2000000  Varies 
   InterpreterTableSize =5000000  48 Bytes (104,166 Interpreter Objects)
   IntegerTableSize     =1000000  16 Bytes (62,500 Integer Objects)
   SymbolTableSize      = 500000  12 Bytes (41,666 Symbol  Objects)

   The amount of memory that AmigaTalk will use depends on how many
   Objects get created by your code, so expect complex operations to
   require more Memory.  My System has 64MB Fast Ram + 16MB on the
   MotherBoard.  ByteArrays & Objects are probably the only
   ToolTypes that you'll need to adjust.
      
   AmigaDOS 3.5+

   Hard disk.
   
